<subSubSection id="CAAE6535FFD4FFBFFF7BFDF1FC73FDC9" box="[189,990,557,627]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" type="description">
<paragraph id="820B36BEFFD4FFBFFF7BFDF1FEB0FDFC" blockId="104.[189,990,557,627]" box="[189,285,557,583]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<heading id="D94381D2FFD4FFBFFF7BFDF1FEB0FDFC" bold="true" box="[189,285,557,583]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFD4FFBFFF7BFDF1FEB0FDFC" bold="true" box="[189,285,557,583]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Habitat</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="820B36BEFFD4FFBFFF7BFD84FC73FDC9" blockId="104.[189,990,557,627]" box="[189,990,600,627]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
Found in leaf litter in 
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFD4FFBFFE78FD85FDACFDC9" box="[446,513,601,626]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFD4FFBFFE78FD85FDACFDC9" box="[446,513,601,626]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Pinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFD4FFBFFDC9FD84FDF1FDC9" box="[527,604,600,626]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFD4FFBFFDC9FD84FDF1FDC9" box="[527,604,600,626]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Betula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFD4FFBFFD53FD84FD4FFDC9" box="[661,738,600,626]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ulmaceae" genus="Ulmus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFD4FFBFFD53FD84FD4FFDC9" box="[661,738,600,626]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Ulmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forests (
<bibRefCitation id="E6254B4FFFD4FFBFFC80FD84FC7CFDC9" author="Shear W. A." box="[838,977,600,626]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref39184" refString="Shear W. A. 1990. On the Central and East Asian milliped family Diplomaragnidae (Diplopoda, Chordeumatida, Diplomaragnoidea). American Museum Novitates 2977: 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1990">Shear 1990</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CAAE6535FFD4FFBFFF7BFD4AFEF2FCA0" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="820B36BEFFD4FFBFFF7BFD4AFE82FD0B" blockId="104.[189,1398,662,795]" box="[189,303,662,688]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<heading id="D94381D2FFD4FFBFFF7BFD4AFE82FD0B" bold="true" box="[189,303,662,688]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFD4FFBFFF7BFD4AFE82FD0B" bold="true" box="[189,303,662,688]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="820B36BEFFD4FFBFFF7BFD1DFEF2FCA0" blockId="104.[189,1398,662,795]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
This is the only chordeumatidan species which occurs inside the area covered by the atlas as well as outside. In addition to the ‘European’ sites, 
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFD4FFBFFD08FD3EFCC0FD40" authorityName="Shear" authorityYear="1990" box="[718,877,737,764]" class="Diplopoda" family="Diplomaragnidae" genus="Diplomaragna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="golovatchi">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFD4FFBFFD08FD3EFCC0FD40" box="[718,877,737,764]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">A. golovatchi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also occurs further east, in western Siberia (
<bibRefCitation id="E6254B4FFFD4FFBFFF01FCDDFEFFFCA0" author="Shear W. A." box="[199,338,769,795]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref39184" refString="Shear W. A. 1990. On the Central and East Asian milliped family Diplomaragnidae (Diplopoda, Chordeumatida, Diplomaragnoidea). American Museum Novitates 2977: 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1990">Shear 1990</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
